The paper discusses a new two-player game based on Sperner's lemma, which is a well-known result in computational geometry and combinatorics. The paper also proves that deciding whether one can win the game is a PSPACE-complete problem, which is a complexity class commonly studied in theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the elegant balance in the game, which suggests that it may be related to game theory, and thus cs.GT (Game Theory) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes other games based on fixed-point theorems, which suggests that it may be related to computational geometry and topology, and thus cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories.
